snippet: Germany’s top public prosecutor said an investigation into whether Chancellor Angela Merkel’s mobile phone had been tapped by American spies had so far failed to find any concrete evidence.
abstract: Germany's top prosecutor Harald Range says investigation into whether American spies tapped Chancellor Angela Merkel's mobile phone has failed to find any concrete evidence.
lead_paragraph: Germany’s top public prosecutor said an investigation into whether Chancellor Angela Merkel’s mobile phone had been tapped by American spies had so far failed to find any concrete evidence.

headline.main: Germany: No Proof Found So Far That U.S. Tapped Merkel’s Phone
headline.print_headline: Germany: No Proof Found So Far That U.S. Tapped Merkel’s Phone
